Ok, I've worked out how to implement some of the breakpoint functions and mixins in a backwards-compatible way.

- The max function can be done similarly to the min functions.
- The down and between mixins can be done similarly to the up mixin.
- The `breakpoint-next` function needs further thought.

Once the functions are all working, this would need to be integrated into the rest of the code base, i.e. pull breakpoint keys from
`$combine-breakpoints` instead of `$grid-breakpoints`. **Question**: Are there any parts of the code base that don't depend on the breakpoint functions and would need to be separately updated?

```scss
$grid-breakpoints: (
        xs: 0,
        sm: 576px,
        md: 768px,
        lg: 992px,
        xl: 1200px,
        xxl: 1400px
) !default;

$vertical-breakpoints: (
        vs: 0,
        vm: 416px,
        vl: 720px,
) !default;

$combine-breakpoints: ();

@each $vname, $vsize in $vertical-breakpoints {
  @if map-has-key($grid-breakpoints, $vname) {
    // This is important; to support singular breakpoints, vertical names must be distinct from the horizontal names
    @error "Invalid Vertical Breakpoint #{$vname} is already used as a Horizontal Breakpoint, Vertical and Horizontal Breakpoint names must be Uniues.";
  }
  @each $hname, $hsize in $grid-breakpoints {
    // Use $hname if both $vsize and $hsize are 0 so all the horizontal names are defined for backwards compatibility
    $name: if($vsize == 0, $hname, if($hsize == 0, $vname, #{$hname}-#{$vname}));
    $combine-breakpoints: map-merge($combine-breakpoints, ($name: [$hsize, $vsize]));
  }
}

@function breakpoint-min-width($name, $breakpoints: $combine-breakpoints) {
  $min: nth(map-get($breakpoints, $name), 1);
  @return if($min != 0, $min, null);
}

@function breakpoint-min-height($name, $breakpoints: $combine-breakpoints) {
  $min: nth(map-get($breakpoints, $name), 2);
  @return if($min != 0, $min, null);
}

@function breakpoint-min($name, $breakpoints: $combine-breakpoints) {
  @return breakpoint-min-width($name, $breakpoints); // Backwards compatibility
}

@function breakpoint-infix($name, $breakpoints: $combine-breakpoints) {
  @return if((breakpoint-min-width($name, $breakpoints) == null) and
             (breakpoint-min-height($name, $breakpoints) == null), "", "-#{$name}");
}

@mixin add_query($query, $value) {
  @if ($value) {
    @media (#{$query}: $value) {
      @content;
    }
  } @else {
    @content;
  }
}

@mixin media-breakpoint-up($name, $breakpoints: $combine-breakpoints) {
  $min-width: breakpoint-min-width($name, $breakpoints);
