Solution we are currently using with 5.3 modals.

```js
window.addEventListener('hide.bs.modal', event => {
    event.target.inert = true
})

window.addEventListener('show.bs.modal', event => {
    event.target.inert = false
})
```

We chose toggling `inert` over invoking `blur()` since the latter (shortened example below) _might_ cause unexpected issues for assistive technology users.

```js
window.addEventListener('hide.bs.modal', () => {
    document.activeElement?.blur()
})
```

