@import "../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/variables";
@import "../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/variables-dark";

// ---> Include any variables that are dependent on the above variables defined in the Bootstrap variables files
$box-shadow: (-$spacer) $spacer 0 $secondary;
```

Because `$spacer` is defined in `scss/variables` so need to be declared before. `$secondary` doesn't depend on another variable defined in `scss/variables`, so you can override it before. It's not really technically an override, it's just that it's declared with your color before, so won't be overriden by the content of `scss/variables`.

