FYI: You _can_ work around this by styling `.form-select` to use `appearance: base-select`, and hide Bootstrap's icon image. The native `::picker-icon` is not hidden through autofill styles. Works only in Chrome/Edge; other browsers will just behave as before.

Example:
```css
@supports (appearance: base-select) {
  .form-select {
    --bs-form-select-bg-img: none;
  }
  .form-select,
  .form-select::picker(select) {
    appearance: base-select;
  }
  .form-select::picker-icon {
    /* styles to render an icon, e.g. from Bootstrap icons */
  }
}
```

See https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn_web_development/Extensions/Forms/Customizable_select for details.

