We can resolve this by ensuring that the tooltip initialization logic is triggered after each page load or hydration in Astro.

In our Astro layout or wherever we handle client-side behavior, make sure to re-initialize tooltips using the Bootstrap API like this:

```js
import { Tooltip } from 'bootstrap';

document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  // Initialize all tooltips
  document.querySelectorAll('[data-bs-toggle="tooltip"]').forEach((el) => {
    new Tooltip(el);
  });
});
```

In some cases with Astro's client-side navigation, you might need to re-run this logic after navigation events if the DOM is updated dynamically.

