This issue is currently tracked as an open bug (#42566) in the upcoming Bootstrap v6 documentation. The core problem is that the syntax highlighter (Chroma) forces a black text color even when the website switches to dark mode, making the code blocks completely invisible against the dark background.Here are the best ways to fix or work around this issue until the official patch is merged:Temporary CSS OverridesYou can fix this immediately in your stylesheet by forcing the syntax highlighter text to use a light color when the dark theme is active

Target the main code container

`[data-bs-theme="dark"] .chroma {
  color: var(--bs-body-color) !important;
}
`
Target the specific unreadable text elements

`[data-bs-theme="dark"] .chroma .n, 
[data-bs-theme="dark"] .chroma .p {
  color: #f8f8f2 !important; /* Forces a light gray/white color */
}
`
